[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Reviewing bean configuration**\n\nI’m analyzing nested public static beans and noting that the native reflection config includes “$” for nested classes. The `BeanMap.clone` method uses `Class.newInstance` on the bean class, which requires a public no-arg constructor. \n\nI’m also looking at how `convertType` works, especially when setting types that might not match. The method attempts to convert values correctly. It's interesting how the use of Integer wrapper from a String could resolve some issues with primitive types. \n\n Lastly, it seems that the `clear` method resets the bean but doesn’t reinitialize maps, which is something to clarify.\n\n**Analyzing clone and newInstance**\n\nI’m looking at how the cloning works, specifically that it replaces the bean and relies on `Class.newInstance`. The clone method iterates through properties, calling get and put to create a clone. I’m wondering if it also copies the class property. \n\nIf there’s no write method, it checks for null. There seems to be a bug where classes have a null write method. I'll need to verify that cloning requires a public no-arg constructor and proper setters, so adding some assertions is a good idea.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0602a48bffbeae510169f965be220081969cecd1b85c8cb9e1\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-WXJj2nNaypsqLnXBTnUo_iXnWyUS3HYyWOIxELSmSNVEicbBAFjCO63wnmzfv71Mk__73DVHCOaMM8DdLPlJPbR_HZbK_4xf2Xr_Y_HckVbGT70UwYcrJACBNUJfv3CE8Na2AAby96GXAE3yswqeikdyDqjs4G6pthnQjzuzO9GLKkdmeKyK_ArB16I8f2UZzeCIMDuukBhS9Z0XUjtgETmVNsZv9dadrYrrel0PnhfkyKmtrgWDy4PLmF3gHYBm7HW3H7Xr9tb01E4z7YTjJkXEUTbKcOgsX4KxnDGgSJ90YjHSC0dPx76FSv6cg1lsziqGO80wwITJ40DPa_jbXzhwMWvzIOHwpDBfSQtNxbwpQncm9jU425O-fpb7foMmXY_lfo4WR9d7OJlkBBLXNSbjnMfJao86YS9ASBQ5nKC5WVLrXvhcB5Bi-sI1O7GrBGPNV13RSjm0Zqc1AJWgAsBayeyujT7axPzyrzeHh-onqMzAhHPp83hXQRSMEs4RFo9XUYoWc1xUd-f5OXwPMRQ0qXqhM430AXvYPvLQPH