e `clear` method resets the bean but doesn’t reinitialize maps, which is something to clarify.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing clone and newInstance**\\n\\nI’m looking at how the cloning works, specifically that it replaces the bean and relies on `Class.newInstance`. The clone method iterates through properties, calling get and put to create a clone. I’m wondering if it also copies the class property. \\n\\nIf there’s no write method, it checks for null. There seems to be a bug where classes have a null write method. I'll need to verify that cloning requires a public no-arg constructor and proper setters, so adding some assertions is a good idea.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_tpsEVmjxnuGFWevzhuY2hJCu|fc_0602a48bffbeae510169f965c9b16881968f0dfa2ce776cbb0", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/commons-collections/commons-collections/2.0/build/reports/dynamic-access/dynamic-access-coverage.json", "limit": 2000}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 371, "output": 723, "cacheRead": 32768, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33862, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777952189158, "responseId": "resp_0602a48bffbeae510169f965bd985c8196bac83565c52cfc04"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_tpsEVmjxnuGFWevzhuY2hJCu|fc_0602a48bffbeae510169f965c9b16881968f0dfa2ce776cbb0", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"classes\" : [ {\n    \"callSites\" : [ {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"org.apache.commons.collections.BeanMap.convertType(Unknown Source)\",\n      \"line\" : null,\n      \"metadataType\" : \"reflection\",\n      \"trackedApi\" : \"java.lang.Class#getConstructor(java.lang.Class[])\"\n    }, {\n      \"covered\" : false,\n      \"frame\" : \"org.apache.commons.collections.BeanMap.clear(Unknown Source)\",\n      \"line\" : null,\n  